& [SLMImplementationFormationGate] is the deferred doorway from SOP contracts to executable implementation
  + [contract_uuid] is d2bfbb84-c987-4e37-85e5-c9db14ffd1af
  + [slice_id] is SLM-12
  + [status] is deferred_until_user_approval
  + [depends_on] is SLM-01 through SLM-11 contract review

  & [FormationPreconditions] is what must be true before coding resumes
    + [contract_coverage] is SLM-01 through SLM-11 accepted or explicitly deferred
    + [source_lineage] is manifest links all governing artifacts
    + [false_start_decision] is reuse, ignore, or delete slm_prototype by explicit user direction
    + [language_choice] is selected for implementation phase
    + [provider_strategy] is mock-only, Ollama, LM Studio, or other adapter selection
    + [test_mapping] is fixture suite mapped to executable tests if implementation begins
    = must: ask for or receive user approval before implementation work
    = must: create file map and module boundary plan before coding

  & [LikelyImplementationShape] is provisional and non-authoritative until formation starts
    + [package] is slm
    + [module] is core data contracts
    + [module] is evidence workspace
    + [module] is providers
    + [module] is provider deliberation
    + [module] is diffusion
    + [module] is wobble
    + [module] is stabilization
    + [module] is semantic graph
    + [module] is primer
    + [module] is fixtures and tests
    ~ [language] is likely Python for executable prototype, but SOP remains reasoning authority

  & [FormationBlockedReason] is why this remains deferred
    + [reason] is user requested specification and project-manager slicing before implementation
    + [reason] is implementation should not proceed until contracts are reviewed

  ~ [Slice12Deferred] is accepted
    @ [support] implementation formation depends on user approval after SOP contract review
